cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since the paper focuses on describing videos using visual data. The second most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper deals with natural language processing. The paper also proposes and trains several network architectures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses different types of image, audio, and video features, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
